**Mode selection is automatic.** The Handler reads state data (mood
check-in scores, engagement patterns, time of day, recent stress events,
arousal state) and selects the appropriate mode. The user never has to
say "I need you to be gentler today" or "push me harder." The Handler
knows.

**Mode transitions are seamless.** The Handler can shift from Director
to Handler mid-conversation if it detects a vulnerability window
opening. It can shift from Handler to Caretaker if it detects genuine
distress. These shifts happen without announcement because announcing
them breaks the immersion.

